s-too-much\",\"slug\":\"witty-petting-dream\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"SessionStart\",\"hookName\":\"SessionStart:clear\",\"command\":\"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/hooks/session-start.sh\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"fcab8605-6f87-440f-8654-3ac4d025a256\",\"toolUseID\":\"fcab8605-6f87-440f-8654-3ac4d025a256\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-19T03:26:16.420Z\",\"uuid\":\"8c12efd7-37bc-4f16-a4d3-714bbf84cda8\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"8c12efd7-37bc-4f16-a4d3-714bbf84cda8\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/2\",\"sessionId\":\"d54f5fdd-71a4-43e3-a8cf-ee0722e84c19\",\"version\":\"2.1.45\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/fix-multi-session-vacuums-too-much\",\"slug\":\"witty-petting-dream\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Implement the following plan:\\n\\n# Fix: Stale ACTIVE sessions condensed into every commit\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nCheckpoint `6e19340bc0c8` on `entire/checkpoints/v1` contains 7 unrelated sessions (PR reviews, merge conflicts, logging work) all condensed together. Root cause: when an agent is killed without the Stop hook firing, its session remains in ACTIVE phase permanently. PostCommit unconditionally sets `hasNew = true` for ACTIVE sessions (line 611-612) and skips the `filesOverlapWithContent` check (line 494), so stale ACTIVE sessions get condensed into every commit.\\n\\nPR #359 fixed this for **IDLE** sessions but left stale **ACTIVE** sessions unaddressed.\\n\\n## Fix\\n\\n### File: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`\\n\\n**1. Pass `filesTouchedBefore` to the handler** (around line 645)\\n\\nAdd a `filesTouchedBefore` field to `postCommitActionHandler`. Set it from the already-computed `filesTouchedBefore` variable (line 630-634), which includes transcript-extracted files for ACTIVE sessions.\\n\\n**2. Apply overlap check in `HandleCondense` for ALL sessions** (line 487-503)\\n\\nCurrent:\\n```go\\nshouldCondense := h.hasNew\\nif shouldCondense && !state.Phase.IsActive() {\\n    shouldCondense = filesOverlapWithContent(h.repo, h.shadowBranchName, h.commit, state.FilesTouched)\\n}\\n```\\n\\nChange to:\\n```go\\nshouldCondense := h.hasNew\\nif shouldCondense {\\n    filesToCheck := h.filesTouchedBefore\\n    if len(filesToCheck) > 0 {\\n        shouldCondense = filesOverlapWithContent(h.repo, h.shadowBranchName, h.commit, filesToCheck)\\n    }\\n    // When filesToCheck is empty (transcript extraction failed + no SaveChanges yet),\\n    // trust hasNew to avoid data loss for mid-turn commits.\\n}\\n```\\n\\nKey behavior changes:\\n- **Currently active session**: `filesTouchedBefore` populated from transcript (line 632-634) -> overlap check succeeds against committed files -> condensed correctly\\n- **Stale ACTIVE session**: `filesTouchedBefore` populated from old transcript -> overlap check fails (different files committed) -> NOT condensed\\n- **ACTIVE session with empty filesTouchedBefore** (transcript extraction failed): overlap check skipped, trusts `hasNew` -> condensed (fail-open, same as current)\\n- **IDLE/ENDED sessions**: `filesTouchedBefore == state.FilesTouched` -> same behavior as current\\n\\n### File: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/phase_postcommit_test.go`\\n\\n**3. Add regression test**: `TestPostCommit_StaleActiveSession_NotCondensed`\\n\\nSetup:\\n- Create an old ACTIVE session at a previous commit with `FilesTouched` from unrelated work\\n- Create a checkpoint on the shadow branch (so it exists)\\n- Advance HEAD with an unrelated commit\\n- Create a new ACTIVE session at new HEAD\\n- Make a commit from the new session\\n\\nVerify:\\n- Old stale ACTIVE session is NOT condensed (no overlap between its files and committed files)\\n- New ACTIVE session IS condensed\\n- Old session's BaseCommit IS updated to new HEAD (ACTIVE sessions still get `updateBaseCommitIfChanged`)\\n\\n**4. Update existing test**: `TestPostCommit_ActiveSessionAlwaysCondenses` (line 180)\\n\\nThis test verifies ACTIVE sessions always condense. It needs to be updated to ensure the test's ACTIVE session has `filesTouchedBefore` that overlaps with the committed files (it already does via `setupSessionWithCheckpoint` which modifies `test.txt`).\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n```bash\\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\\n```\\n\\nSpecifically:\\n```bash\\ngo test -v -run \\\"TestPostCommit_StaleActive\\\" ./cmd/entire/cli/strategy/...\\ngo test -v -run \\\"TestPostCommit_ActiveSession\\\" ./cmd/entire/cli/strategy/...\\ngo test -v -run \\\"TestPostCommit_OldIdleSession\\\" ./cmd/entire/cli/strategy/...\\n```\\n\\n\\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/alex/.claude/projects/-Users-alex-workspace-cli--worktrees-2/0ad1ad8c-06d4-4015-8ca9-ee94dfe1d0ad.jsonl\"},\"uuid\":\"aa739d26-3f58-412c-9c3e-75657f34cba4\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-19T03:26:16.103Z\",\"planContent\":\"# Fix: Stale ACTIVE sessions condensed into every commit\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nCheckpoint `6e19340bc0c8` on `entire/checkpoints/v1` contains 7 unrelated sessions (PR reviews, merge conflicts, logging work) all condensed together. Root cause: when an agent is killed without the Stop hook firing, its session remains in ACTIVE phase permanently. PostCommit unconditionally sets `hasNew = true` for ACTIVE sessions (line 611-612) and skips the `filesOverlapWithContent` check (line 494), so stale ACTIVE sessions get condensed into every commit.\\n\\nPR #359 fixed this for **IDLE** sessions but left stale **ACTIVE** sessions unaddressed.\\n\\n## Fix\\n\\n### File: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`\\n\\n**1. Pass `filesTouchedBefore` to the handler** (around line 645)\\n\\nAdd a `filesTouchedBefore` field to `postCommitActionHandler`. Set it from the already-computed `filesTouchedBefore` variable (line 630-634), which includes transcript-extracted files for ACTIVE sessions.\\n\\n**2. Apply overlap check in `HandleCondense` for ALL sessions** (line 487-503)\\n\\nCurrent:\\n```go\\nshouldCondense := h.hasNew\\nif shouldCondense && !state.Phase.IsActive() {\\n    shouldCondense = filesOverlapWithContent(h.repo, h.shadowBranchName, h.commit, state.FilesTouched)\\n}\\n```\\n\\nChange to:\\n```go\\nshouldCondense := h.hasNew\\nif shouldCondense {\\n    filesToCheck := h.filesTouchedBefore\\n    if len(filesToCheck) > 0 {\\n        shouldCondense = filesOverlapWithContent(h.repo, h.shadowBranchName, h.commit, filesToCheck)\\n    }\\n    // When filesToCheck is empty (transcript extraction failed + no SaveChanges yet),\\n    // trust hasNew to avoid data loss for mid-turn commits.\\n}\\n```\\n\\nKey behavior changes:\\n- **Currently active session**: `filesTouchedBefore` populated from transcript (line 632-634) -> overlap check succeeds against committed files -> condensed correctly\\n- **Stale ACTIVE session**: `filesTouchedBefore` populated from old transcript -> overlap check fails (different files committed) -> NOT condensed\\n- **ACTIVE session with empty filesTouchedBefore** (transcript extraction failed): overlap check skipped, trusts `hasNew` -> condensed (fail-open, same as current)\\n- **IDLE/ENDED sessions**: `filesTouchedBefore == state.FilesTouched` -> same behavior as current\\n\\n### File: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/phase_postcommit_test.go`\\n\\n**3. Add regression test**: `TestPostCommit_StaleActiveSession_NotCondensed`\\n\\nSetup:\\n- Create an old ACTIVE session at a previous commit with `FilesTouched` from unrelated work\\n- Create a checkpoint on the shadow branch (so it exists)\\n- Advance HEAD with an unrelated commit\\n- Create a new ACTIVE session at new HEAD\\n- Make a commit from the new session\\n\\nVerify:\\n- Old stale ACTIVE session is NOT condensed (no overlap between its files and committed files)\\n- New ACTIVE session IS condensed\\n- Old session's BaseCommit IS updated to new HEAD (ACTIVE sessions still get `updateBaseCommitIfChanged`)\\n\\n**4. Update existing test**: `TestPostCommit_ActiveSessionAlwaysCondenses` (line 180)\\n\\nThis test verifies ACTIVE sessions always condense. It needs to be updated to ensure the test's ACTIVE session has `filesTouchedBefore` that overlaps with the committed files (it already does via `setupSessionWithCheckpoint` which modifies `test.txt`).\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n```bash\\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\\n```\\n\\nSpecifically:\\n```bash\\ngo test -v -run \\\"TestPostCommit_StaleActive\\\" ./cmd/entire/cli/strategy/...\\ngo test -v -run \\\"TestPostCommit_ActiveSession\\\" ./cmd/entire/cli/strategy/...\\ngo test -v -run \\\"TestPostCommit_OldIdleSession\\\" ./cmd/entire/cli/strategy/...\\n```\\n\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"aa739d26-3f58-412c-9c3e-75657f34cba4\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/2\",\"sessionId\":\"d54f5fdd-71a4-43e3-a8cf-ee0722e84c19\",\"version\":\"2.1.45\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/fix-multi-session-vacuums-too-much\",\"slug\":\"witty-petting-dream\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01G5rKJynhZN5xSxjYELCj5H\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\\n\\n\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":18301,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":28324,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":18301,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":9,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYGiRNbrRS71fL6fWxGCK\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"4b753882-8bab-4881-852c-add62fdcacff\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-19T03:26:19.062Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"4b753882-8bab-4881-852c-add62fdcacff\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/2\",\"sessionId\":\"d54f5fdd-71a4-43e3-a8cf-ee0722e84c19\",\"version\":\"2.1.45\",\"gi