sTouched` directly without the `committedFileSet` intersection or content overlap check. A stale ENDED session with `FilesTouched` set would still be condensed into unrelated commits via this path.\\n\\nHowever, looking at the state machine: ENDED sessions only reach `HandleCondenseIfFilesTouched` when `ctx.HasFilesTouched` is true (line 229). And PR #359 already fixed the `hasNew` check for IDLE sessions via `sessionHasNewContent`. ENDED sessions that have been properly stopped would have accurate `FilesTouched`. So this is a lower-risk path — stale ENDED sessions are less common than stale ACTIVE ones (you'd need the agent to call Stop but then get killed before the commit). **Not a blocker but worth noting for future hardening.**\\n\\n### Test Coverage\\n\\n- **`TestPostCommit_StaleActiveSession_NotCondensed`** — Good regression test. Correctly sets up two concurrent sessions (stale + new), commits only the new session's files, and verifies:\\n  - Stale session NOT condensed (StepCount preserved)\\n  - Stale session BaseCommit IS updated (correct — ACTIVE sessions get base updated)\\n  - New session IS condensed\\n  - `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch exists\\n\\n- **`TestHandleTurnEnd_PartialFailure` fix** — The change from `setupSessionWithCheckpoint` to explicit `SaveChanges` with `second.txt` as a new file is the right fix. The old test was masking a real gap — the second commit's `committedFileSet` contained only `second.txt`, but the session's `FilesTouched` only had `test.txt`.\\n\\n### Style & Conventions\\n\\n- Comments are thorough and explain the \\\"why\\\" well\\n- The `testNewActiveSessionID` constant extraction for `goconst` is clean\\n- Follows existing patterns (using `setupSessionWithCheckpoint`, `commitFilesWithTrailer`, etc.)\\n\\n### Minor Nits\\n\\n1. **Line 510: `committedTouchedFiles` allocation** — Could pre-allocate with `make([]string, 0, len(h.filesTouchedBefore))` to avoid growing, but this is a hot-path-irrelevant allocation in a git hook. Not worth changing.\\n\\n2. **Test at line 1504+**: The test doesn't use `t.Parallel()`, but looking at other tests in this file, none of them do since they all call `t.Chdir(dir)` which is incompatible with parallel execution. Consistent.\\n\\n### Risks\\n\\n- **Low risk of regression for normal ACTIVE sessions**: Mid-turn commits from an active agent will have `filesTouchedBefore` populated (from `state.FilesTouched` or transcript extraction), and those files WILL be in `committedFileSet` since the agent's commit includes its own changes. The intersection will be non-empty, and `filesOverlapWithContent` will confirm the match.\\n- **Fail-open for empty `filesTouchedBefore`**: If transcript extraction fails AND no `SaveChanges` has occurred, the old behavior (condense unconditionally) is preserved. This is the right default.\\n\\n### Verdict\\n\\nThe changes are correct and well-tested. The core fix is sound — intersecting session files with actually-committed files before the content overlap check cleanly distinguishes stale sessions from active ones. The one gap (`HandleCondenseIfFilesTouched` for ENDED sessions) is low-risk and out of scope for this fix.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1169,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":80384,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":1169,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYGkU2cdYrAac9oiqeq4Z\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"e1516d54-4df3-4402-a90d-2b0f1183e609\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-19T03:53:36.140Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"e1516d54-4df3-4402-a90d-2b0f1183e609\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/2\",\"sessionId\":\"d54f5fdd-71a4-43e3-a8cf-ee0722e84c19\",\"version\":\"2.1.45\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/fix-multi-session-vacuums-too-much\",\"slug\":\"witty-petting-dream\",\"ty